OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782762496
OL,3,CFrance's record heatwave led to 1,000
OL,4,Cexcess deaths in days, officials say
OL,6,FHeat records were toppled in several
OL,7,Fcountries over the weekend, as Germany
OL,8,Fhit 41.7C and Poland baked under its
OL,9,Fnew all-time high of 40.5C.
OL,11,FDenmark, which marked new records of
OL,12,F37C (98.6F) on Saturday, saw 1,156
OL,13,Flighting strikes by Sunday morning,
OL,14,Faccording to public broadcaster DR.
OL,16,FThe Czech Republic also experienced
OL,17,Fits hottest day ever with 41.9 C
OL,18,F(107.4 F), up from the previous record
OL,19,Fof 40.9C (105.6F) on Saturday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
