OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782762496
OL,3,CFrance's record heatwave led to 1,000
OL,4,Cexcess deaths in days, officials say
OL,6,FWildfires were sparked in a large
OL,7,Fforest contaminated with ammunition
OL,8,Ffrom World War Two near Gohrischheide,
OL,9,Feastern Germany.
OL,11,FSimilarly, a major firefighting
OL,12,Foperation was underway in the German
OL,13,Fvillage of Traisen, where the heat
OL,14,Fsparked a forest fire in an area that
OL,15,Falso contained unexploded ordnance.
OL,17,FFirefighters had to stop work
OL,18,Ftemporarily after explosions took
OL,19,Fplace and a disposal unit was brought
OL,20,Fin to continuously assess the
OL,21,Fsituation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
